parameters:
Mel: I'll gather other materials just in
case. Be careful, okay?

Zerachiel: It's okay because Sachia is
here.

Sachia: I'll do my best not to
disappoint your expectations.
Mel: Has it been a day since then...

Azel: The attack on the magic capital of
Vaal has caused tension to skyrocket in
the surrounding countries.

Unié: ...The scars left by the angels
run deep, don't they?

Ishvald: Many citizens are stunned with
anxiety and fear...

Claudia: As expected, the attack on the
magic continent's capital has caused a
great shock...

Sachia: Moreover, it's a fact that even
the Demon King's castle has been
invaded.

Rabi: The choir hasn't been captured
either, so they might attack again,
don't you think?

Lala: Well, it's no wonder the anxiety
doesn't disappear, huh...

Azel: ...What's even more dangerous is
the baseless rumor that the Holy Kingdom
was behind the angels.
Mel: We're at a dead end.

Mel: In the first place, I just returned
home after a long time, so my older
sisters should be the ones inheriting.

Mel: Father, who is the Demon King, is
not here, and everyone, I wonder what
they're doing...

Unié: Since long ago, both the Demon
King and the princesses have been free-
spirited...

Ishvald: ...If they hear the rumors of
the attack on the magic continent, they
will surely come back.

Azel: Until the Demon King returns, we
have no choice but to protect the magic
continent ourselves.

Zerachiel: It's really difficult to say
this in the context of this
conversation...

Zerachiel: I'm thinking of returning to
Logres.

Zerachiel: Thanks to everyone, the
curse-breaking potion is also complete.
Mel: You should hurry and return home.

Mel: Is Lady Effy being targeted, I
wonder?

Zerachiel: Yes, in three days... no,
it's already two days from now.

Zerachiel: Sarial said that they will
attack Logres in two days.

Zerachiel: I'm worried about Aries too,
and I want to go back soon, but there's
a problem...

Zerachiel: Even if we travel by ship, it
will take two weeks to get to Logres.
Lala: Then we won't make it in time!!

Zerachiel: Yeah, that's right. I've been
wondering what I should do.

Mel: How are Sarial and the others able
to travel to Logres in three days?

Zerachiel: More accurately, it's the
Absorb Gate.

Zerachiel: There are teleportation gates
that connect the world we live in to
various places in this world, and if we
pass through them, we can move to
different locations in a short period of
time.

Lala: But you know, it consumes a huge
amount of elements.

Lala: Because it also has a significant
negative impact on the environment, its
use is generally prohibited unless
ordered by the higher-ups.

Zerachiel: Even if we occupy the
teleportation gate from now on, we'll be
ambushed at the destination and it will
be the end.

Claudia: Moving to Logres in two days is
not realistic...

Azel: Do you know about the Mountain of
Mythical Beasts?
Rabi: I've heard of it before.

Rabi: Isn't it the place where the evil
divine beasts created by the god of
destruction were sealed long ago?

Mel: What about the Mountain of Mythical
Beasts?

Azel: Even now, in the Mountain of
Mythical Beasts, divine beasts are still
sleeping, frozen in ice.

Azel: ...The name of the divine beast is
Marnagarm.

Azel: The only existence with the power
to move coordinates.

Claudia: Moving the coordinates... is it
possible to teleport?

Azel: I believe that with the power of
Marnagarm, we can send Zerachiel to
Logres.

Mel: It's quite a forceful method, isn't
it...

Claudia: On top of that, it's a one-way
trip.

Azel: Yes, I don't think it's possible
to return to the Demon Continent once we
teleport.

Zerachiel: If we can make it in time to
fend off Sariel's attack, let's go with
that method.

Lala: I'm going too. I want to settle
things with Remiel.
Azel: Then let's go with a small group.

Azel: Claudia-san is well-versed in
magic, so could we ask for your
assistance with the teleportation?

Claudia: Yes, I don't mind. If I can be
of help, I would be happy to assist.

Azel: We can't take Mel-sama to a
dangerous mountain.

Claudia: So, you're saying it's fine if
I do it?
Azel: Ah, no! It's not like that!!

Mel: Fuhahahaha! The plan is settled,
isn't it?!

Mel: We're heading to the mountain of
mythical beasts from here. Be careful,
okay?
Sachia: Rabi and I will help Mel.

Sachia: Without the captain, the
security is also weak.
Rabi: Yes, go and come back safely.

Zerachiel: Everyone, thank you for
taking care of me. Thank you.
